      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "YASENA (10) was handy on the corner but couldn't maintain the pressure and weakened late when resuming over 900m at Wellington last start. Yet place in four first-up outings but always improves thereafter. Big chance with that run under the belt over an extra 100m. DON'T SAY DO (5) returns after a 20-week break. Returned some decent figures last prep, albeit when second and third-up. Not a lot of depth to this maiden so a big run will not surprise. OAKFIELD MARS (8) last appeared when fourth in a busy finish over 1400m at Dubbo on 2 February. Comes to hand quickly and has performed at this trip in the past. Capable of figuring in the finish. The lightly raced RUAIRI (1) has been handy on straightening but failed to finish off in his two runs this prep. Fitter now and can offer a bit more in the concluding stages. BEAUTY SUPERB (4) has not raced since failing on debut at Wyong in December. Resumes in an easier race with blinkers on so expect a bit more this time.",
